data.name: Classic Waffles
data.quickTastyDescription: Fluffy and golden-brown waffles, perfect for breakfast or brunch, topped with your favorite syrup.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your waffle iron according to manufacturer's instructions.
In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt.
In another bowl, combine the milk, eggs, vegetable oil, and vanilla extract.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Do not overmix; lumps are okay.
Lightly grease the waffle iron with butter or cooking spray.
Pour the batter onto the preheated waffle iron and cook according to the manufacturer's instructions until golden brown and crispy.
Carefully remove the waffle and repeat with the remaining batter.
Serve warm with syrup, fruit, or your favorite toppings.
